250 g Ground Turkey
2 unit(s) Egg
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
56 g Baby Spinach
113 g Yellow Onion, chopped
¼ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
2 unit(s) Ciabatta Roll
2 tbsp Hot Sauce
½ cup Milk*
4 tbsp Unsalted Butter*

Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch strips.
Whisk together eggs and 1/2 cup (1 cup) milk together in a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.

Heat a large or medium non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When the pan is hot, add 1 (2 tbsp) butter, then turkey, onions and pepper.
Cook, breaking up turkey into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Add spinach. Cook, stirring often, until wilted and any extra liquid as evaporated from veggies, 2-3 min.

Spread the turkey and veggies out evenly in the pan. Reduce heat to medium.
Carefully pour the egg mixture over top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and cook until eggs are set, 3-4 min.

Halve ciabatta. Toast in a toaster until desired doneness. Spread each toasted ciabatta half with 1/2 tbsp butter.
Divide turkey and egg skillet between plates.
Drizzle over hot sauce if desired.

If you've opted to get turkey, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the sausage.**